# Prompt: Checkvist Responsive App (React / React Native / Expo)

## Project Overview
Build a responsive application that serves as a modern UI layer on top of the existing Checkvist REST API (https://checkvist.com/auth/api). The app must work seamlessly as:

1. **A web PWA** — installable on Android/iOS home screens via the browser.
2. **A native Android app** — distributed via APK or Play Store.
3. **A native iOS app** — distributed via App Store or TestFlight.

All three targets share a **single codebase** using **Expo + React Native Web**. Web is the primary development target; native is an additive concern layered on top.

This is **Phase 1**. Implement only the features described below. Architect the code so additional Checkvist features (notes/comments, tags, bulk import, etc.) can be added later without rewriting core modules.

---

## Tech Stack

### Cross-Platform Core (Expo)
- **Expo SDK 52+** with the **New Architecture** (Fabric / JSI) enabled.
- **React Native** for native iOS/Android; **React Native Web** for browser output.
- **Expo Router v4** (file-based routing, works on web + native — replaces React Router).
- **TypeScript** (strict mode) across all targets.
- **NativeWind v4** — Tailwind CSS class names compiled to React Native `StyleSheet` at build time; the same `className` props work on web and native.
- **TanStack Query v5** — server state, caching, background refetch (runs identically on all targets).
- **Zustand v5** — local UI state (auth, active checklist, expanded task rows, view mode).
- **Axios** with token-injection + auto-refresh interceptor.
- **date-fns v4** — date arithmetic and formatting.
- **react-hook-form v7 + Zod v4** — form validation on login and task creation.
- **lucide-react-native** — icon set (same icon names as lucide-react; different import path for native).

### Web-Only Additions
- **`@expo/webpack-config`** or Expo's built-in Metro web bundler for the web build.
- **`vite-plugin-pwa`** (or Expo's `expo-web-pwa` preset) for service worker + manifest generation.
- **`@tanstack/react-virtual`** — list virtualization (web only; native uses `FlashList`).

### Native-Only Additions
- **`@shopify/flash-list`** — high-performance list for iOS/Android (replaces `FlatList`).
- **`expo-secure-store`** — encrypted token storage on native (replaces `localStorage` on web).
- **`expo-splash-screen`** + **`expo-status-bar`** — native chrome.
- **`react-native-gesture-handler`** + **`react-native-reanimated`** — smooth animations and gesture handling (long-press, swipe, drag).

### Build & Distribution
- **EAS Build** for iOS and Android binaries.
- **EAS Update** (OTA) for JS-layer patches without App Store review.
- **Vercel** for the web/PWA target (zero-config, `expo export --platform web`).
- A single `eas.json` defines `development`, `preview`, and `production` profiles.

