## Core Feature: Task List Sorted by Due Date

### View Modes
The task list header has a **three-mode toggle** (persisted to storage):

| Icon | Mode | Description |
|------|------|-------------|
| `LayoutList` | **Date view** (default) | Flat rows grouped under collapsible date headers (Overdue · Today · Tomorrow · This week · Later · No due date). Each task appears in the bucket matching its own due date. |
| `AlignLeft` | **Outline view** | XMind-style hierarchical outline. Root tasks at the left margin; children indented 24 px per level with a faint vertical guide. No date grouping — pure tree. Priority badge and due date shown inline right of the title. |
| `Network` | **Mind map view** | Interactive SVG/Canvas tree. The active checklist name is the virtual root node. Root-level tasks branch left-to-right; children recurse. Nodes are colour-coded by priority. Supports pan + pinch-to-zoom with preset zoom levels (10 % – 500 %). A **Fold All / Unfold All** toolbar button collapses or expands all nodes at once. Clicking a node navigates to its detail view. |

All three modes share the same `buildTaskTree` data layer and the same expand/collapse state store.

### Date View — Detail

#### Sorting & grouping
- Top-level rows sorted ascending by due date; nulls at the bottom.
- Six collapsible date buckets: **Overdue**, **Today**, **Tomorrow**, **This week**, **Later**, **No due date**.

#### Task row
- Completion checkbox, task content (with **inline Markdown rendering** — bold, italic, code, strikethrough, links — via `InlineMarkdown`), priority badge (1–10, red/amber/green), humanized due date, expand chevron if the task has children.
- Checking the checkbox calls `POST /…/tasks/{id}/close` with optimistic UI + rollback toast on failure.

#### Hierarchy in date view
- Every task appears as a top-level row in its own date bucket.
- Tasks with children show a `+` / `−` chevron (left of checkbox). Expanding reveals the full descendant subtree inline, ordered by Checkvist `position`.
- A child with its own due date appears **both** at the top level (in its date bucket) and nested under its parent when expanded — intentional duplication.
- Indent: ~20 px per depth level with a faint vertical guide.
- Expanded/collapsed state persisted in storage keyed by task id.
- Virtualize the top-level rows (web: `react-virtual`; native: `FlashList`). Expanded subtrees render inline.

### Outline View — Detail
- Renders the full task tree from `buildTaskTree` roots.
- Each row: expand chevron, task content (inline Markdown), priority badge, due date.
- Children indented 24 px per level.
- Leaf nodes show a larger bullet; parent nodes show a bracketed child count suffix (e.g. `· [3]`).
- Clicking task content navigates to the detail view.
- No date grouping; no completion checkbox (use the detail view for that).

### Mind Map View — Detail
- SVG/Canvas tree rendered on an unbounded canvas.
- Virtual root node = active checklist name (styled distinctly).
- Root-level tasks branch off the virtual root; children recurse left-to-right.
- Node appearance: rounded rectangle, title text with `stripMarkdown` (HTML not supported in SVG `<text>`), priority colour fill or border, due date below title if set.
- Edges: curved bezier connector lines.
- Layout constants: root node 220×60, task nodes 180×36, 72 px horizontal gap, 12 px vertical sibling gap, 28 px group gap.
- **Zoom presets**: 10, 20, 50, 80, 100, 120, 150, 200, 300, 400, 500 % — toolbar select or pinch gesture.
- **Fold All / Unfold All** button in the toolbar.
- Pan: drag the canvas background. Pinch-to-zoom on touch.
- Clicking/tapping a node navigates to that task's detail view.

