## Acceptance Criteria
1. I can log in with my Checkvist email and API key on all three targets (web, iOS, Android) and stay logged in across reloads / app restarts.
2. I see my tasks from the default checklist, grouped and sorted by due date (**Date view**).
3. I can switch to **Outline view** and see the full task hierarchy with inline Markdown, priority, and due date — no date grouping.
4. I can switch to **Mind Map view**, pan and zoom the SVG canvas, fold/unfold all nodes, and click a node to open its detail view.
5. Tasks render flat-by-due-date with hierarchy layered on top. Every task appears as a top-level row in the bucket matching its own due date. Expand/collapse state survives a reload/restart.
6. Inline Markdown (bold, italic, code, strikethrough) renders correctly in task content across all three views.
7. Right-clicking (desktop) or long-pressing (mobile/native) a task opens the context menu to set priority or change due date.
8. Tapping the due date opens the 3×3 quick date picker; all nine options work and persist.
9. I can create a new task from the top of the list (or FAB on native/mobile), and it appears immediately and persists.
10. Clicking a task's content opens the detail view at the correct route. It shows editable title, priority, due date, sub-task tree with inline Markdown, and an "Add sub-task" input. Deep-linking works on reload (web) and cold start (native).
11. On web, the app is installable as a PWA. On native, the EAS build runs and the app installs on a physical device.
12. Offline: previously loaded tasks and checklists are visible when the network is unavailable.

